<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">They're pretty easy to slow now at level 70.  Even at 65 if shamans were using balance of the nihil they could land slow pretty easily.  Kiters to split up the traps help immensely and if your knights are capable of tanking the trapmobs its vastly easier than trying to use wars.
<br />

<br />
We used to use the pet only for the barxt fight.  Now our dps is sufficient to kill him without getting any adds even without the pet, but at level 65 it helped quite a bit.  We would have 2 enchanters on charm, with the one that wasn't controlling the pet at the time chain clicking the charm button.  We also tried using the pet to help clear traps but in tight spaces it was too dangerous.
<br />

<br />
I think with the nerf to shadowstep in uqua you can no longer use the pet only for the barxt fight so its probably pretty useless now.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
